## Step 9 — Initial EF Core Migration

**Prerequisites:** The docker-compose postgres container must be running. You do not need the database to exist yet — EF Core creates it.

```bash
# Install the dotnet-ef global tool if not already installed
dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef

# Verify it is available
dotnet ef --version

# From the solution root (important — dotnet ef needs to find the startup project)
cd /Users/fbeleta/Documents/WebIde/Web_ide

# Create the first migration
dotnet ef migrations add InitialSchema \
    --project WebIde.Api \
    --startup-project WebIde.Api \
    --output-dir Data/Migrations

# Apply the migration to the database (docker postgres must be running on localhost:5432)
dotnet ef database update \
    --project WebIde.Api \
    --startup-project WebIde.Api
```

This will create:
```
WebIde.Api/Data/Migrations/
├── <timestamp>_InitialSchema.cs
├── <timestamp>_InitialSchema.Designer.cs
└── AppDbContextModelSnapshot.cs
```

To start fresh at any point:
```bash
# Wipe and recreate the database
dotnet ef database drop --project WebIde.Api --startup-project WebIde.Api --force
dotnet ef database update --project WebIde.Api --startup-project WebIde.Api
```

